00:18:13.060 --> 00:18:18.400
&gt;&gt; Gutsi Putu Sudarta: I'm going
to talk today about the story

00:18:18.400 --> 00:18:23.060
of Sutasoma and the place
and describe [inaudible]

00:18:23.060 --> 00:18:26.400
who played the story
through his poetry.

00:18:26.400 --> 00:18:30.770
During the [inaudible] in
the central Balinese kingdom

00:18:30.770 --> 00:18:34.970
of [inaudible], Sutasoma
is believed

00:18:34.970 --> 00:18:39.870
to be the grandson
of [inaudible].

00:18:39.870 --> 00:18:45.190
The last king mentioned in
the Hindu Mahabharata epic.

00:18:45.190 --> 00:18:50.480
The story combines elements
of Hinduism and Buddhism

00:18:50.480 --> 00:18:53.230
and Sutasoma himself is
thought to be the [inaudible].

00:18:53.230 --> 00:18:59.360
The supreme Buddha in the
[inaudible] tradition.

00:18:59.360 --> 00:19:04.610
Today the story is well-known in
Bali especially in the village

00:19:04.610 --> 00:19:10.310
of [inaudible] with its
history of Buddhists priests.

00:19:10.310 --> 00:19:17.390
And among the flowers
[inaudible] that combines Hundi,

00:19:17.390 --> 00:19:24.580
Buddhists, and Muslim elements.

00:19:24.580 --> 00:19:25.880
[Inaudible] in this
story [inaudible]

00:19:25.880 --> 00:19:28.490
or Balinese religion.

00:19:28.490 --> 00:19:33.230
As this thing from
Indian tradition

00:19:33.230 --> 00:19:37.000
because it combines
many different beliefs

00:19:37.000 --> 00:19:41.230
and for most religious
pluralism.

00:19:41.230 --> 00:19:47.170
The story of Sumasota begins
with Purusada, an honorable king

00:19:47.170 --> 00:19:50.800
who enjoys hunting [inaudible].

00:19:50.800 --> 00:19:55.710
This is Purusada.

00:20:00.540 --> 00:20:05.660
Purusada enjoyed eating the
animals he hunted and one day

00:20:05.660 --> 00:20:10.730
of his assistants accidentally
cut his finger while cooking the

00:20:10.730 --> 00:20:16.360
animal he cut bleeding
into the food.

00:20:16.360 --> 00:20:21.750
[Inaudible] found this meal
the most delicious and it awoke

00:20:21.750 --> 00:20:25.960
in him an animal
nature that grew --

00:20:25.960 --> 00:20:27.620
&gt;&gt; Andy McGraw: Ferociously.

00:20:27.620 --> 00:20:32.500
So the assistant
cut his own fingers.

00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:34.900
Not [inaudible].

00:20:34.900 --> 00:20:38.370
&gt;&gt; Gusti Puti Sudarta: He
became addicted to the taste

00:20:38.370 --> 00:20:40.050
of human flesh and begin

00:20:40.050 --> 00:20:45.040
to become a cruel ruler
enforcing corporal punishment

00:20:45.040 --> 00:20:47.000
to feed his habit.

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:51.180
Slowly he became
[inaudible], an ogre.

00:20:51.180 --> 00:20:57.740
One day, [inaudible] endured
himself in [inaudible]

00:20:57.740 --> 00:21:02.040
so he asked for help

00:21:02.040 --> 00:21:06.730
from [inaudible] the
god of time and death.

00:21:06.730 --> 00:21:15.700
Kali demanded the corpses
of 100 kings in [inaudible]

00:21:15.700 --> 00:21:22.040
and so [inaudible] begin to
wage war across the country

00:21:22.040 --> 00:21:24.920
in the form of the
[inaudible] ogre, [inaudible].

00:21:24.920 --> 00:21:29.330
[Inaudible] like that.

00:21:30.510 --> 00:21:47.950
[ Laughter ]

00:21:47.950 --> 00:21:50.960
Eventually Kali demanded
Sutasoma,

00:21:50.960 --> 00:21:56.800
the king of the [inaudible]
as a sacrifice as well.

00:21:56.800 --> 00:22:03.520
[Inaudible] as you know is
very handsome king like that.

00:22:03.520 --> 00:22:05.320
[Inaudible].

00:22:05.320 --> 00:22:15.040
[ Singing ]

00:22:15.040 --> 00:22:19.250
Very handsome and
very fine character.

00:22:22.400 --> 00:22:26.300
So Sutasoma's brother-in-law
Dasabahu,

00:22:26.300 --> 00:22:29.570
this character Dasabahu.

00:22:29.570 --> 00:22:36.020
[Inaudible].

00:22:36.020 --> 00:22:42.930
Dasabahu was given a
bone by Lord Brahma

00:22:42.930 --> 00:22:47.730
and Purusada was given a
bone by Lord [inaudible],

00:22:47.730 --> 00:22:50.140
a manifestation of Shiva.

00:22:50.140 --> 00:22:53.370
Because they were
both very powerful,

00:22:53.370 --> 00:22:58.040
they were destroy
the environment.

00:22:58.040 --> 00:23:02.190
It looked like a
nuclear wasteland.

00:23:02.190 --> 00:23:05.250
Eventually Purusada
defeated Dasabahu.

00:23:05.250 --> 00:23:10.000
When Sutasoma came out of
the court to face Prusada,

00:23:10.000 --> 00:23:14.480
all of the flowers
begin to bloom again.

00:23:14.480 --> 00:23:19.080
The aura of the Buddha
brought the land back to life.

00:23:19.080 --> 00:23:22.700
When Purusada saw this
he suddenly became aware

00:23:22.700 --> 00:23:27.830
of what he had become and
asked, "Why have I done this?

00:23:27.830 --> 00:23:31.230
Why have I become [inaudible]?"

00:23:31.230 --> 00:23:36.020
Purusada begged Sutasoma
for forgiveness and asked

00:23:36.020 --> 00:23:38.330
to become his disciple.

00:23:38.330 --> 00:23:41.630
But Sutasoma first
offered himself a sacrifice

00:23:41.630 --> 00:23:45.820
to [inaudible] who
became an innermost dragon

00:23:45.820 --> 00:23:49.120
in [inaudible] and swallow him.

00:23:52.980 --> 00:23:59.510
[Inaudible] already transformed
to be the giant dragon.

00:23:59.510 --> 00:24:12.310
[ Growling ]

00:24:12.310 --> 00:24:24.170
Just as he swallowed
Sutasoma's feet [inaudible]

00:24:24.170 --> 00:24:30.150
that time cannot eat Suma
because it's the Buddha.

00:24:30.150 --> 00:24:33.580
It transcends time itself
and so like Purusada

00:24:33.580 --> 00:24:36.240
and [inaudible] begged
for forgiveness and asked

00:24:36.240 --> 00:24:38.250
to become his disciple.

00:24:38.250 --> 00:24:49.640
The story of Sutasoma includes
very important poem called the

00:24:49.640 --> 00:24:52.510
[inaudible] structures
[inaudible].

00:24:52.510 --> 00:25:01.040
[ Singing ]

00:25:01.040 --> 00:25:04.240
&gt;&gt; Andy McGraw: This is a very
creative translation here.

00:25:04.240 --> 00:25:06.320
It's said that there
are two truths.

00:25:06.320 --> 00:25:09.510
One known as Buddha
and one as Shiva.

00:25:09.510 --> 00:25:16.040
[ Singing ]

00:25:16.040 --> 00:25:17.730
And they appear different

00:25:17.730 --> 00:25:22.510
but in fact spiritual truth
cannot be split in two.

00:25:22.510 --> 00:25:32.260
[ Singing ]

00:25:32.260 --> 00:25:35.300
Truly the essence of
Buddhism and Shivaism are one.

00:25:35.300 --> 00:25:37.100
The deepest truth.

00:25:37.100 --> 00:25:46.040
[ Singing ]

00:25:46.040 --> 00:25:47.630
It's difference is
only apparent.

00:25:47.630 --> 00:25:49.420
In diversity there is oneness.

00:25:49.420 --> 00:25:51.340
An essence that cannot
be divided

00:25:51.340 --> 00:25:54.730
because it encompasses
everything.

00:25:54.730 --> 00:25:58.250
&gt;&gt; Gutsi Putu Sudarta: In Bali
this poem is often sung during

00:25:58.250 --> 00:25:59.550
the [inaudible].

00:25:59.550 --> 00:26:02.250
It evokes a feeling

00:26:02.250 --> 00:26:06.680
of a beautiful blooming
spring transition.

00:26:06.680 --> 00:26:09.750
Now this idea of
religious pluralism,

00:26:09.750 --> 00:26:14.550
[inaudible] essential
oneness has in my opinion,

00:26:14.550 --> 00:26:19.280
a very strong moral
ethics and it relates

00:26:19.280 --> 00:26:27.190
